---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Bhutan Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/bhutan/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Nepal for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/nepal' },
  { title: 'India for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/india' },
  { title: 'Thailand for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/thailand' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'bhutanFit', header: 'Bhutan Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'BTN$37,500-53,550/mo', bhutanFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'BTN$43,875-62,680/mo', bhutanFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'BTN$33,750-48,195/mo', bhutanFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'BTN$31,375-44,815/mo', bhutanFit: 'Very Good' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'BTN$33,750-53,550', annual: 'BTN$405K-642.6K' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'BTN$46,300-71,400', annual: 'BTN$555.6K-856.8K' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'BTN$62,250-95,850', annual: 'BTN$747K-1.15M' },
  { category: 'Required Tourist Fee', monthly: 'BTN$16,800/day', annual: 'Part of visit' },
  { category: 'Medical Evacuation', monthly: 'N/A', annual: 'BTN$500K-1.5M' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Bhutan 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors visiting Bhutan. Gross National Happiness, Himalayan beauty, limited healthcare, and coverage for tourists 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Bhutan"
  subheadline="Bhutan offers unique Gross National Happiness philosophy, stunning Himalayan monasteries, preserved Buddhist culture, and carbon-negative environment—a transformative spiritual destination, not retirement residence."
  heroImage="/images/countries/bhutan-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Visit Bhutan</h2>
  <p>
    Bhutan offers unique Gross National Happiness focus, pristine Himalayan landscapes, preserved Buddhist culture, and the world's only carbon-negative country. Note: Bhutan does not allow foreign retirement or long-term residence—visits only through expensive guided tours.
  </p>

  <p>
    Thimphu is the capital. Paro has the famous Tiger's Nest monastery. Punakha offers beautiful dzongs. All visits require licensed tour operators and $200/day Sustainable Development Fee. Extended retirement not possible.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Visitors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Very limited; India evacuation common</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Dzongkha; English in tourism</li>
      <li><strong>Cost:</strong> $200/day SDF minimum + tour costs</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Alpine; cold winters</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Buddhist; sustainable; isolated</li>
      <li><strong>Residence:</strong> NOT available for foreigners</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Bhutan Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Bhutan healthcare is very limited—Jigme Dorji Wangchuck National Referral Hospital in Thimphu is main facility. Basic care only. Altitude can affect seniors. Serious conditions require evacuation to India (Delhi, Kolkata) or Bangkok. High altitude (2,300m+) challenging.
  </p>

  <p>
    Government provides free healthcare to citizens but very basic. No private hospitals. International insurance with strong evacuation coverage essential. Travel insurance with high-altitude coverage and evacuation mandatory.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Critical: Not a Retirement Destination</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Bhutan does NOT allow foreign residence or retirement. All visits require licensed tour operators and $200/day Sustainable Development Fee. Maximum stay limited. Healthcare very basic with India evacuation needed for serious conditions. Visit only—not live.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options</h2>
  <p>
    Bhutan has controlled tourism:
  </p>

  <h3>Tourist Visa</h3>
  <p>
    Arranged through licensed tour operator. $200/day Sustainable Development Fee. Visa approved with tour booking.
  </p>

  <h3>No Long-Term Options</h3>
  <p>
    No retirement, residence, or extended stay options for foreigners. Tourism only model.
  </p>

  <h3>Indian Nationals</h3>
  <p>
    Indians can visit without SDF and with more flexibility. Regional exception.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Bhutan:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Entry:</strong> Travel insurance strongly recommended</li>
    <li><strong>High altitude:</strong> Coverage for altitude sickness essential</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> India evacuation coverage critical</li>
    <li><strong>Tour coverage:</strong> Part of tour arrangement</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Bhutan</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      Comprehensive travel insurance with high-altitude coverage and India evacuation essential. Healthcare very limited locally. Ensure policy covers altitude-related conditions. Tour operators may require proof of coverage.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors visiting Bhutan, evacuation coverage critical:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Bhutan</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong Asia network, India evacuation</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>High altitude:</strong> Ensure coverage for altitude conditions</li>
    <li><strong>India access:</strong> Delhi/Kolkata evacuation routes</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Travel Insurance Quote</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage for Bhutan visit.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Bhutan visits (BTN pegged to INR, ~83 to USD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Total Visit Cost Considerations</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>$200/day SDF:</strong> Required for all non-Indian tourists</li>
    <li><strong>Tour operator:</strong> Additional costs for guide, accommodation</li>
    <li><strong>Insurance:</strong> Essential additional cost</li>
    <li><strong>Total:</strong> Bhutan is expensive to visit</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: Spiritual Seeker, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> 2-week Buddhist pilgrimage tour. Guided visit.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global travel insurance with altitude coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Total cost:</strong> ~$4,000-6,000 for 2 weeks including SDF, tour, insurance.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: Photography Enthusiast, 71</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> 10-day photography tour. Tiger's Nest focus.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global with premium evacuation.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Total cost:</strong> ~$3,000-4,500 for 10 days all-inclusive.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Indian Senior, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> 3-week extended visit. No SDF required.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care with India home coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Total cost:</strong> Much lower without SDF; insurance ~INR$35,000/week.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I retire to Bhutan?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        No—Bhutan does not allow foreign retirement or long-term residence. Tourism only model. All visits require licensed tour operators. $200/day Sustainable Development Fee. Maximum stay limited. Beautiful to visit; impossible to live.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Why is Bhutan so expensive?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Sustainable tourism policy—$200/day SDF limits tourist numbers, protects environment and culture. "High value, low volume" approach. Fee supports free education, healthcare, environmental protection. Premium destination by design.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is the altitude challenging for seniors?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—Thimphu is 2,334m, Paro 2,200m. Higher passes even more. Altitude sickness risk real. Acclimatization important. Some monasteries require hiking. Consult doctor before visiting. Not suitable for those with heart/lung conditions.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Bhutan worth it?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        For many, yes—truly unique experience. Pristine environment, preserved culture, Buddhist philosophy, stunning scenery. Transformative for right person. Expensive but once-in-lifetime experience. Not for budget travelers.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for Bhutan travel coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Bhutan does not allow foreign residence—visits only through licensed tour operators. Always verify current requirements with your tour operator and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
